the properties of the junctions between the host chromosome and the
Integration has two junctions: left and right. At each junction there may be a gap (unexplained
bases inserted), an overlap (homology between the host and viral sequences), or a clean junction
(neither a gap nor an overlap). Gaps, overlaps and clean junctions are mutually exclusive at each
junction. There may be a number of bases deleted from the host chromosome at the site of the
integration, and these are always the bases immediately after the right junction
: probability that a junction will contain common bases between the host and viral
: probability that a junction will contain random bases at the jucntion between the host
: mean of a Poisson distribution, used to decide the nubmer of bases involved
in the junction. Regardless of the number drawn from the distribution, the number of bases is
zero if the junction is neither a gap nor an overlap (a 'clean' junction), and more than zero if the
junction is a gap or an overlap
: probability that the integration involves a deletion from the host chromosome
: mean of Poisson distriubtion from which the number of bases deleted from
the host chromosome is drawn. Regardless of the number drwan from this distribution, the
number of bases is zero if the integration is not associated with a deletion from the host

If chunk_props['n_delete'] is greater than zero, split chunk into chunk_props['n_frag'] pieces and delete specified number of these pieces (but not the first or last pieces)

To rearrange a ViralChunk, pick a number, i, between 1 and n-1 (where n is the nubmer of pieces), and swap all the self.pieces to the left of i with all of those to the right
To split into pieces, pick a number of breakpoints between self.start and self.stop., b1, b2, ..., and self.pieces becomes [[self.start, b1], [b1, b2], ... [bn, self.stop]]
To delete a piece, choose a number, i, between 1 and 1-n (where n is the number of pieces), and delete self.pieces[i] and self.oris[i]
Pick random orientations for each piece, so self.oris becomes a list with length len(self.pieces) and entries of either '+' or '-'
